comment.body:
This looks like a step in the right direction: Adding cpu_features to the overall build and using it initially to detect compile-time features. When the Linux CI builds also pass (CXX packages to be added to the docker images) I'd say this PR is OK. 

@xvzcf, I'd defer to you as to when to include this: Please also let me know whether you'd add CXX to the Linux CI images or whether I should do it. If you want to do it before pushing the docker add-on, the package targets to be added are `[yum install] gcc-c++` for Centos and `[apt-get install] g++` for Ubuntu/Debian

Next step after this then is using the package for runtime feature detection _within_ the code.
